{"id":14881663,"mediaExerciseId":"d0c90724-503d-4262-8d8c-0d2c734047c5","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"19.4","sectionTitle":"Managing Cash Disbursements","pageNumber":655,"solutions":[{"id":5999207,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"**a)** Maximizing disbursement float is a sound business practice and is based on writing checks, for example, in a geographically distant bank, which increases the time required to realize checks. In that way, the time of realization of the check is delayed, and the money that is someone else's is still in possession. But this practice is debatable from both an ethical and an economic point of view. For example, frequent payment terms offer a significant early payment discount that gives you a bigger discount than any savings from playing a float game. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**   A zero-balance account is an account that the bank maintains only for payment and to which it pays money from the main account of the company only if it is necessary to cover the check.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/d6cb9df83334d2c7cc4fde54858464db/fe91446a058dc15379261991a285d7a2/lateximg_large.png","width":657},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/d6cb9df83334d2c7cc4fde54858464db/fe91446a058dc15379261991a285d7a2/lateximg.png","width":328}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"2711d101-7c77-4960-a9bd-76dcb821302a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","